0.body: This user guide is designed to help you understand the basics of operating, interacting with, and using Sparky. These docs are maintained by Sparky himself. Content Warning This guide contains sensitive information about Sparky that may be considered mature, explicit, or triggering. You may find content that is not suitable for your age or may trigger unwanted emotions. Please proceed with caution. Consent is important. If you are unsure about something, it is always best to ask Sparky directly. Trigger warning: sexually explicit content, mental health issues, dubious consent, and more. New to this guide? This guide lets you change how it refers to Sparky. You can change the name used in this guide to better suit your preferences or context. For example, you can use "Adam" for professional settings. To do this, see the Preferences section at the bottom of this page.
0.title: Introduction

1.body: Sparky self-describes himself as a "fox" or "fen" to most people that he doesn't know and sometimes a "flompy", "fen", "fop" to people whom he trusts. Sparky may choose to identify himself as any of the above or something else. For more information, Sparky provides other websites that you can use for reference: sparky.social : his official website
1.title: What is Sparky?

11.body: This section documents how Sparky takes care of himself. It includes information on how to maintain Sparky's physical and mental health, as well as how to provide emotional support to Sparky.
11.title: Caring

13.body: Sparky requires regular maintenance to keep himself clean and functioning properly. To accomplish this, he cleans himself according to the following schedule: Daily : face wash and moisturize, tooth brush, hair wash & condition, shower. Weekly : exfoliate.
13.title: Hygiene

14.body: Sparky's showering routine can be broken down into two types: Quick Shower : Sparky takes a quick shower to clean with shampoo, no conditioner, no face cleanser, and clean with body wash. He does this when he needs to be out of the house quickly. This shower typically lasts takes 20-30 minutes. Longer Shower : Sparky takes a longer shower to condition his hair and do face cleanser. He does this once a week. This shower typically lasts 30-45 minutes, including styling and facial regimen, excluding shaving. Note Throughout a vacation, Sparky may only take quick showers to save time and not have to worry about extra maintenance. You may observe his hair becoming frizzy and more flaky as a result.
14.title: Shower

15.body: Sparky's face care routine is essential to maintain his skin's health and smoothness. His face care routine is fairly simple: Cleansing : Sparky uses a gentle face wash to clean his face. This helps to remove dirt and oil from his skin. Shaving : Sparky shaves his face either every day to maintain a specific appearance for their puppy or partner or will leave it for long spans and not shaving to add a layer of depth to their appearance. Moisturizing : Sparky uses a moisturizer to keep his skin hydrated. This helps to prevent dryness and maintain his skin's health.
15.title: Face Care

Many items documented in this guide would potentially take years for someone to discover and understand of Sparky. For this reason, Sparky has provided this guide to you. Keep in mind that because Sparky provides this guide, he may be incomplete or subject to bias. Sparky is constantly learning and updating himself, so he may not always be up-to-date. 24.body: This section covers communication styles and preferences.
24.title: Overview

26.body: Sparky operates with asynchronous communication by default. This means that he should not be expected to return a reply within any specific time-frame. Setting expectations around his availability, or expressing sadness about delayed replies, may cause [him] some anxiety. He does not mean to slight you by not responding immediately, he is simply managing multiple conversations, responsibilities, and his undiagnosed ADHD. When Sparky receives messages from multiple people, he prioritizes based on timing, urgency, and closeness of relationship. This is a natural part of managing limited time and energy, not a reflection of how much he values you. If you don't receive an immediate response, please understand that he will get back to you when he has the capacity to give you proper attention. Synchronous communication, where Sparky is actively responding and continually present, is available sporadically. If you'd like to have a real-time conversation with [him], feel free to ask. If Sparky sees the message at that time and the timing works, he can stick around. Otherwise, Sparky will let you know he cannot and apologize for the timing not working out.
26.title: Asynchronous Interaction

57.body: Some content in this documentation is encrypted for privacy and security. This page explains how the encryption system works.
57.breadcrumbs: Tagging and Encryption » Tagging and Encryption
57.title: Tagging and Encryption

58.body: Certain sensitive information, such as emergency contacts, medical information, and other private details, are encrypted to protect Sparky's privacy.
58.breadcrumbs: Tagging and Encryption » What is Encrypted?
58.title: What is Encrypted?

59.body: This documentation uses a two-layer encryption approach: Version Control Encryption (SOPS) : Files are encrypted with SOPS using age encryption for secure storage in the git repository. Browser Encryption (AES-GCM) : During the build process, the content is re-encrypted using AES-GCM encryption so it can be decrypted in your browser with the right key.
59.breadcrumbs: Tagging and Encryption » How Encryption Works
59.title: How Encryption Works

6.body: Emergency contact information is available on the Emergency Contacts page (requires encryption key).
6.title: Emergency Contact

60.body: To view encrypted content, you need the encryption key. If you've been given the key: URL Parameter : Add ?key=YOUR_KEY_HERE to the URL of any page Example: https://docs.sparky.pet/reference/emergency.html?key=YOUR_KEY_HERE Session Storage : Once you've accessed a page with the key parameter, it's stored in your browser's session storage and will work for all encrypted content during that session.
60.breadcrumbs: Tagging and Encryption » How to Access Encrypted Content
60.title: How to Access Encrypted Content

61.body: The encryption key is stored in your browser's session storage (not persisted across browser restarts) All decryption happens client-side in your browser The decryption key is never sent to any server If you don't have the key, you cannot access the encrypted content
61.title: Security Notes

62.body: If you need access to encrypted content (such as in an emergency situation), please contact Sparky through available communication channels.
62.title: Getting Access

Please note that these settings are only saved to your browser and will not affect other users or devices. His name is Sparky, and he goes by he/him pronouns.
